Moberly School District
September 1 at 1:38 PM ·

The following letter was emailed to staff and parents today after the District received notification of one confirmed case of Coronavirus Disease 2019 (COVID-19) at Moberly School District. Cleaning and disinfecting of the exposed location have been completed, and the individual is in quarantine and being monitored.

District and Randolph County Health Department administrators are conducting thorough contact investigations and notifying those staff and parents of students who may have been in the proximity of the affected individual. At the time of this posting, a limited number of students at the Middle School, High School, and Gratz Brown Elementary have been identified for possible exposure and contacts are underway.

Here's the schedule for when you can turn in chromebooks, chargers and school items for student personal belongings. Please abide by the grade level times so that we can maintain proper safety for everyone. This will be done valet style which means you'll stay in your vehicle. We'll come to you to exchange the school belongings for student personal belongings. Email Mr. Samuel with questions. If you have students in multiple grade levels, we'll exchange everything at once so you don't have to make multiple trips. Other than this we will be strict about the schedule to limit the amount of people around the building and cars in the streets.

shared_text:
Moberly School District
April 9 at 5:44 PM ·

Dear Moberly Spartan family,

With the health and wellbeing of our students, staff, and community in mind, the Governor of Missouri announced this afternoon that no Missouri public schools will reopen to conduct in-person classes for the rest of the 2019-2020 school year. However, meal service and eLearning will continue for Moberly School District through the remainder of the school calendar. We will share more details about this next week.

This extended school closure leaves us with so many questions and concerns, and a lot to digest. Please know we are diligently working on detailed plans for the rest of this school year as we continue navigating and adapting in this most unusual situation. Stay tuned for answers and additional information about eLearning, semester grading, end of school year events, gathering personal belongings from buildings, and more. Visit www.moberly.k12.mo.us for additional updates throughout the coming weeks.

Thank you for your continued support!

Moberly School District
March 26 at 1:05 PM ·

This letter was emailed to district parents today regarding an extended school closure through April 24, 2020. Key points contained in Dr. Miller’s letter are:

· Schools are not scheduled to reopen until April 27th.
· Virtual Learning in Google Classroom will officially begin March 30th .
· Grab and Go meal service will continue weekdays throughout the district closure.
· Any questions or concerns about virtual learning should be directed to your child’s teacher and/or principal after spring break.
· Continue to follow the advice of our health officials.

Thank you for your continued support and understanding in these unusual times. Stay safe, stay home and stay well!

Moberly School District
March 26 at 1:05 PM ·

Thank you for your continued support and understanding in these unusual times. Stay safe, stay home and stay well!

post_text:
On Tuesday, October 29th, award-winning author Mary Casanova will be visiting our school! She'll be giving a talk on what it's like to be an author and maybe bringing some of her puppet friends. Thanks to the Moberly Public Schools Foundation Grant for making this happen. Three of Miss Casanova's books will be available for purchase and autographing:

'Hush Hush, Forest' A beautifully illustrated tale of the woods at night, $17.00

'One-Dog Canoe' How many animals can fit in a little boat? $19.00

'Utterly Otterly Day' What happens when little Otter wanders away from his mother? $19.00

If your child would like to purchase a book, please have them bring cash or a check to school on October 29th. Checks MUST BE MADE OUT TO BARNES AND NOBLE or we cannot accept them.

Visit Mary Casanova on the web: www.marycasanova.com
